meta {
  name: [APISIX] allow BRP write - JWT with read and write scope
  type: http
  seq: 8
}

docs {
  EXPECTED behaviour once the auth-zen APISIX plugin is implemented.

  The plugin should:
    1. Extract the subject from the Bearer JWT (scopes: ["brp:read", "brp:write"]).
    2. Map the HTTP method (PUT) to action "write".
    3. Receive an allow decision from the policy agent.
    4. Forward the request to the upstream and return its response to the client.

  The JWT payload used here decodes to:
    { "sub": "municipality-case-api", "organization": "urn:nl:gov:rotterdam",
      "assurance_level": "high", "roles": ["municipality_caseworker"],
      "scopes": ["brp:read", "brp:write"] }
}

put {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/anything
  body: json
}

